AB  - This chapter explores the transformative role of neural networks and graph models in optimizing traffic and energy systems within modern cities. As urban demands grow, advanced AI-d riven algorithms are essential for enhancing traffic management, incident prediction, and efficient energy distribution. The chapter reviews recent advancements, including convolutional neural networks, graph neural networks, and reinforcement learning, and discusses emerging challenges like data privacy, scalability, and the integration of IoT for real-time monitoring. Future research directions focus on quantum neural networks and sustainable urban planning, offering insights into developing resilient, efficient infrastructures for smart cities.
