AB  - Besides a good prediction a classifier is to give an explanation how the input data is related to the classification result. There is a general agreement that logic expressions provide a better explanation than other methods like SVM, logistic regression, and neural networks. However, a classifier based on Boolean logic needs to map continuous data to Boolean values which can cause a loss of information. In contrast, we design a quantum-logic-inspired classifier where continuous data are directly processed and the laws of the Boolean algebra are maintained. As a result from our approach we obtain a CQQL condition which provides good insights into the relation of input features to the class decision. Furthermore, our experiment shows a good prediction accuracy.
