AB  - The proceedings contain 35 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Analysis of Experimental Algorithms. The topics include: Improved Contraction Hierarchy Queries via Perfect Stalling; constraint Generation Algorithm for the Minimum Connectivity Inference Problem; Efficient Split-Radix and Radix-4 DCT Algorithms and Applications; analysis of Max-Min Ant System with Local Search Applied to the Asymmetric and Dynamic Travelling Salesman Problem with Moving Vehicle; computing Treewidth via Exact and Heuristic Lists of Minimal Separators; fast Public Transit Routing with Unrestricted Walking Through Hub Labeling; effective Heuristics for Matchings in Hypergraphs; Approximated ZDD Construction Considering Inclusion Relations of Models; efficient Implementation of Color Coding Algorithm for Subgraph Isomorphism Problem; the Complexity of Subtree Intersection Representation of Chordal Graphs and Linear Time Chordal Graph Generation; quantum-Inspired Evolutionary Algorithms for Covering Arrays of Arbitrary Strength; an Experimental Study of Algorithms for Geodesic Shortest Paths in the Constant-Workspace Model; searching for Best Karatsuba Recurrences; minimum and Maximum Category Constraints in the Orienteering Problem with Time Windows; internal Versus External Balancing in the Evaluation of Graph-Based Number Types; hacker’s Multiple-Precision Integer-Division Program in Close Scrutiny; assessing Algorithm Parameter Importance Using Global Sensitivity Analysis; a Machine Learning Framework for Volume Prediction; faster Biclique Mining in Near-Bipartite Graphs; k-Maximum Subarrays for Small k: Divide-and-Conquer Made Simpler; computing a Minimum Color Path in Edge-Colored Graphs; a Faster Convex-Hull Algorithm via Bucketing; fixed Set Search Applied to the Minimum Weighted Vertex Cover Problem; automated Deep Learning for Threat Detection in Luggage from X-Ray Images; student Course Allocation with Constraints.
