AB  - We propose a method that utilizes Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) models for predicting continuous physical observables. While CNN models are typically used for solving classification problems, our method utilizes the soft labels of CNN models to predict high-dimensional data. In this study, we successfully apply this method to predict the transmission probability data of a quantum-dot chain system as a function of energy. To optimize the model performance, we explore three different sampling schemes to construct the training datasets. Furthermore, we compare the performance of CNN models with that of Feed-Forward Neural Network models. Our results clearly demonstrate the potential of using soft labels in CNNs for high-dimensional data prediction and highlight the advantages of adaptive sampling technique to improve model's performance.
